               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gospel of Matthew (fols. 3ra-48ra)
 - Bǝsrāta Mātewos “Gospel of
                     Matthew” (fols. 3ra-48ra)
 - Short postscript (fol. 48ra)
 II) Gospel
                     of Mark (fols. 48ra-74ra)
 - List of the “tituli” for the Gospel of Mark:
                     49 titles (fol. 48ra-vb)
 - Bǝsrāta Mārqos (fols. 49ra-74ra)
 - Short
                     postscript (fol. 74ra)
 III) Gospel of Luke (fols. 74ra-111vb)
 - List
                     of the “tituli” for the Gospel of Luke (fol. 74ra-vb). 
 - List of the
                     “tituli” for the Gospel of Luke: 80 titles (fol. 75ra-vb).
 - Bǝsrāta Luqās
                     “Gospel of Luke” (fols. 76ra-111vb)
 IV) Gospel of John (fols.
                     112ra-137ra)
 - Bǝsrāta Yoḥannǝs “Gospel of John” (fols. 112ra-136vb,
                     l.18)
 - Short postscript on the truthfulness of the Gospels (fol. 136vb,
                     ls.19-21)
 - Postscript to the Gospel of John (fols. 136vb, l.22-137ra,
                     l.4).
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The “tituli” are numbered only when they precede the Gospel text;
                        within the text itself the chapters are not numbered. The number of the
                        “tituli” for the Gospel of Mark (47) is given erroneously.</note>
                     <note>- The introduction to the Four Gospels is missing.</note>
                     <note>- The canon tables are missing.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
