                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#111vb2">f. 111vb, l.2</locus>
                           <desc>. Blessing for the persons mentioned.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#111vb2">111vb, l.2</locus>: ወከማሁ፡ ይባርኮ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ለገብሩ፡
                              አቡነ፡ አስተአ፡ ድንግል፡ ወአቡሁ፡ አቡነ፡ አሥራተ</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#111vb">111vb</locus>: And likewise may God bless His
                              servant ʾabuna ʾAstäʾa Dǝngǝl and his father ʾabuna ʾAśrāta …</quote>
                           <note> Written as continuation and part of the preceding Gospel text.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#137ra">f. 137ra</locus>
                           <desc>-rb. Record concerning a reconciliation agreement and punishment
                              for its transgressors (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Written in difficult language, a mixture of
                           Amharic and Gǝʿǝz. The reconciliation took place on Maskaram 21, 1889
                           E.C. (September 30, 1896 A.D.). The note was written down on Ṭǝqǝmt 1
                           (October 10). The note mentions rās<note> Mängäša (Yoḥannǝs, d. 1906
                              A.D.), governor of Tǝgray in 1889-1906, as well as a number of
                              geographical locations, including Mǝʾsar Gʷǝhila and ʿAddiqäḥarsi.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>. Note: መጽሐፈ፡ ሕንኪ፡ አለሽ፡
                           በወርሐ፡ መጋቢት፡ ተጽሕፈት፨
 - <locus target="#78r">78r</locus>, 78v, 79r,
                           79v, etc. Marginal notes repeating chapter titles.
 - <locus target="#92r">92r</locus>, 95v, in the upper margin. Corrections in
                           red (?).
 - <locus target="#136v">136v</locus>, 137r, in the bottom
                           margin. Pen trials.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
